## Design System: iOS 26 Liquid Glass

⚠️ **Note**: This project now uses a unified design system. See `design-system.mdc` for component usage.

### Core Principles
- Implement iOS 26 Liquid Glass design language
- Use backdrop-filter for authentic glass effects
- Layer glass elements above content, never within main content flow
- Apply glass effects to navigation, toolbars, floating buttons, and overlays
- Ensure glass elements adapt to background content dynamically
- Maintain accessibility with proper contrast ratios (WCAG AA: 4.5:1 minimum)
- Use rounded corners that match modern iOS interface design
- Implement smooth transitions (300ms standard)

### Liquid Glass Classes

**Use existing classes from `globals.css`:**

```tsx
// Standard glass card
<Card className="liquid-glass-card liquid-glass-card-elevated">
  <div className="liquid-glass-content p-6">
    Content
  </div>
</Card>

// Interactive glass card
<Card className="liquid-glass-card liquid-glass-card-interactive liquid-glass-card-refraction">
  <div className="liquid-glass-content p-6">
    Interactive content
  </div>
</Card>

// Glass modal
<Modal className="liquid-glass-modal">
  Content
</Modal>
```

### CSS Implementation Guidelines

**Glass Effect Structure:**
```css
/* Base glass card */
.liquid-glass-card {
  backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
  border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3);
  box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(31, 78, 112, 0.12);
}

/* Interactive states */
.liquid-glass-card-interactive:hover {
  transform: translateY(-4px);
  box-shadow: 0 16px 48px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12);
  transition: all 300ms cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
}
```

### Responsive Design
- Mobile-first approach
- Breakpoints: sm (640px), md (768px), lg (1024px), xl (1280px)
- Test on both light and dark themes
- Ensure touch targets are minimum 44x44px (Apple HIG standard)

### Accessibility Requirements

**WCAG AA Compliance:**
- All interactive elements must have proper ARIA labels
- Maintain 4.5:1 contrast ratio for text
- Keyboard navigation must work for all features
- Focus states must be clearly visible (2px blue outline)
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`
- Support `prefers-contrast: high`

**Automatic Features:**
```tsx
// All interactive elements auto-sized
button, a, [role="button"] {
  min-height: 44px;
  min-width: 44px;
}

// Focus ring automatically applied
*:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid rgba(42, 150, 209, 0.6);
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

// Motion preferences respected
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  * {
    transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
  }
}
```

